comments:
In the alien words, the first half related to the shape and the second half to the colour. I would repeat the word out loud to try and memorise which suffix/affix pertained to which qualities. Learning the rule of red was the hardest as it changed spelling for different shapes and picking up the pattern was hard as it wasn't shown very often or consistently.

I assume that the "other person" was not real, but either way they were very frustrating.
